<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Bayern Munich forward Kingsley Coman is set to miss Friday's Bundesliga opener against Schalke as he is self-isolating at home after he had contact with a person infected with coronavirus. </p>

<p>The German giants confirmed the France winger would need to spend 'a period in isolation' and will undertake remote virtual training sessions.</p>

<p>Coman, who has been identified by Manchester United as potential alternative to Jadon Sancho, tested negative for the coronavirus on Sunday. </p>

<p>Bayern Munich forward Kingsley Coman had contact with a person infected with coronavirus</p>

<p>After a press conference on Tuesday, Bayern issued a statement in English in which they stated Coman would miss the Schalke game but a German version did not include that detail.  </p>

<p>In the statement, Bayern said: 'The 24-year-old attacker has been in contact with a person infected with the coronavirus and is in now undertaking a period of isolation at home, in accordance with the guidelines outlined by the Robert Koch Institute and in coordination with the Health Department of the City of Munich. </p>

<p>'Coman will keep himself fit at home with remote virtual training sessions.'</p>

<p>Coman scored the only goal of the game when Bayern beat Paris Saint-Germain 1-0 in the Champions League final last month. </p>

<p>Coman scored the winner when Bayern beat PSG in the Champions League final last month</p>
